vegetables wash and trim off the top
green portion of the leeks and since
that parts a little tough you can save
that piece for making soup or stock then
slice and chop the remaining white
portion of the leeks into small pieces
we'll need about 1 cup of chopped leeks
for this recipe
next in a medium-sized bowl start with
half a pound of ground pork we're going
to season the pork filling with quarter
teaspoon of sugar half a teaspoon of
salt half a teaspoon of grated ginger 1
tablespoon of low-sodium soy sauce 1
teaspoon of sesame oil 1 tablespoon of
minced garlic because I love garlic and
1 tablespoon of cornstarch once you have
the ingredients in the bowl I find its
easiest to just mix and knead together
the filling with your hands
finally add in your chopped leeks after
the leeks are mixed in let's prep for
wrapping the potstickers prepare a small
bowl of water for dipping along with
some paper towels start by placing the
potsticker wrapper in one palm scooping
in a small amount of filling about one
tablespoon is good then dip your finger
in a bit of water and wet the outer
edges of the wrapper next fold over and
pleat the potstickers together to ensure
a tight seal I'm doing about five to six
pleats starting from left to right when
you're done your pot stickers should
look like this then continue wrapping
until you've used up all your filling
after you've wrapped all your pot
stickers including any extras that you
may want to freeze for later it's time
to cook
pre-heat a nonstick pan over medium heat
add in 1 tablespoon of oil and carefully
place the pot stickers in the pan next
add in 2/3 cups of water and cover with
the steaming lid during this time we're
going to steam the pot stickers for 6
minutes or until most of the water
evaporates then when all of the water is
almost gone remove the lid and let them
continue cooking and browning for a few
more minutes until they're slightly
crisp on the bottom when they're done
the pot stickers should be browned and
easy to remove with tongs or spatula
finally I like to serve these pot
stickers hot with a side of chili garlic
sauce
